race.comment: INCY VINCY (9) made an encouraging debut finishing 3.5L from the winner over 1000m at Muswellbrook. Did a good job after settling back and is sure to improve. Can get off the mark this time. WENDOUREE (3) returns after six months in the paddock. Placed his only fresh outing and went well enough at Armidale following. Has a low barrier and the tongue tie on for the first time. He's up to this. SPIRIT OF DESTINY (2) debuts and hasn't been seen since a trial in March. Has been given time, and the betting will be key with him. Ditto MADAM SO LATAIRE (6), who has switched from a Victorian stable on an 82-day return. May need it but is better suited up here.
